[[File:Bundesarchiv Bild 102-09786, Erstes Gleitflugzeug Otto Lilienthals.jpg|thumb|200px| Gustav Lilienthal and a replica of Otto's glider, 1930]]'''Gustav Lilienthal''' (October 9, 1849 &ndash; February 1, 1933) was a German [[Reform movement|social reformer]], a pioneer in building and construction technology ([[Prefabricated building]]s), inventor of different [[Construction set]]s (e. g. [[Anchor Stone Blocks]]) and involved in the pioneering work  of his brother, [[Otto Lilienthal]] in aviation.<ref>{{cite news |author= |coauthors= |title=Gustav Lilienthal, Flight Pioneer, Dies. With Famous Brother, Otto, He Experimented With Flying Machines in the 90s. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1933/02/02/archives/gustav-lilienthal-flight-pioneer-dies-with-famous-brother-otto-he.html |quote=Gustav Lilienthal, a pioneer in German aviation and a brother of the famous Otto Lilienthal, died today at the age of 83. ... |newspaper=[[United Press]] in the [[New York Times]] |date=February 2, 1933 |accessdate=2010-12-06 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author= |coauthors= |title=G. Lilienthal, Air Pioneer, Dies In Germany At 83 |url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/chicagotribune/access/442692252.html?dids=442692252:442692252&FMT=CITE&FMTS=CITE:AI&type=historic&date=Feb+02,+1933&author=&pub=Chicago+Tribune&desc=G.+LILIENTHAL,+AIR+PIONEER,+DIES+IN+GERMANY+AT+83&pqatl=google |quote= |newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]] |date=February 2, 1933 |accessdate=2010-12-06 }}</ref>

