'''Margaret Smith Polson''' (''[[née]]'' Murray; [[Paisley, Scotland|Paisley]] July 20, 1865 – January 27, 1927 [[Montreal]]), better known as '''Margaret Polson Murray''', was a Canadian social reformer, magazine editor and founder of the [[Imperial Order Daughters of the Empire]].{{sfn|Gillett|2005}}{{efn|Also known as Mrs Clarke Murray in some sources {{harv|Small|1995|p=76}}, because she was married to [[John Clark Murray]] (a professor at [[McGill University]]).}}

